			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: I'll never get it...<a name="31205"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 28 04 5:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Anyways, does anyone have any tips at all that will help me into have more courage?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I would say courage to enter unfamiliar or dangerous zones comes from a process that involves two primary things.  
<br />

<br />
First, the  more effective you are playing your bard, the more comfortable you'll be.  Bards are the shiznit for exploring dungeons: lull, charm, mezz--you name it, you've got it.  Lull is definitely your best friend in a dungeon.  At level 63 you can get the Fading Memories AA, and this along with the song Highsun will make exploring a lot easier.
<br />

<br />
Second, become familiar with the zone itself.  You say you're in a good, family type guild.  Get groups and adventure into zones you're interested in--and observe.  Do the mobs see through invis?  Are they social mobs (group aggro), static spawns, roamers?  Are there casters, summoning mobs?  What levels are they?  How many hitpoints do they have?  Try to become familiar with the layout of the place.  Keep going back until it becomes second nature.  Instead of porting out, ask the group if they'd mind fighting their way out.
<br />

<br />
Regarding your specific issue in entering Sol A, the mobs in there should be like gnats biting an elephant.  Just swat them.  When I went in there to do my turn-in, I'd never been there before.  I used lull, and if I got aggro, I killed the mob.  If I started getting adds, I charmed the original target.  That was it.  The hardest part was avoiding falling into the lava--lol.  Just bring a gate potion or have some way of porting out so you don't have to run through it again unless you want to. Hopefully you get the general idea.  Good luck.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
