				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually, what I have found is the best way to gain self assurance and courage, is to find something that you think is just out of your reach, and doing it. When I went to Chardok for first time to camp my halfling mask, first thing I did was to study the map. Once I was ready to go down, I asked a couple of necros in guild if they could come summon me if I messed up and died. I always make sure I have a 'backdoor', a way out somehow, if it's a gate potion, or someone online who can come help me if things go wrong. And once you achieve your goal, you'll be ready to do something harder the next time around.
